---
title: "PII Redactor: Complete Data Flow"
---
flowchart TD
    RAW["Raw data with sensitive info\n(network configs, logs, reports)"]
    SCAN["PII Redactor scans for patterns\n(30+ regex rules)"]
    DECIDE{"Decision per data type"}

    PRESERVE["PRESERVE as-is\n(private IPs, vendor domains)"]
    MAP["MAP to safe tokens\n(public IPs → 10.99.x.x\nhostnames → device-X\ncustomers → Customer-X)"]
    DESTROY["DESTROY permanently\n(passwords, API keys, secrets\n→ [REDACTED])"]

    MERGE["Sanitized data assembled"]
    CONTEXT["Context injection header prepended\n\"This data has been sanitized.\nTreat 10.99.x.x as public endpoints...\""]
    AI["AI processes safely\n(never sees original sensitive data)"]
    RESPONSE["Response with mapped tokens"]
    RESTORE{"Optional: Restore\n(token store lookup)"}
    FINAL["Final output with real data restored\n(passwords stay [REDACTED])"]

    RAW --> SCAN
    SCAN --> DECIDE

    DECIDE -->|"Safe to share"| PRESERVE
    DECIDE -->|"Hide but keep relationships"| MAP
    DECIDE -->|"Too dangerous"| DESTROY

    PRESERVE --> MERGE
    MAP --> MERGE
    DESTROY --> MERGE

    MERGE --> CONTEXT
    CONTEXT --> AI
    AI --> RESPONSE
    RESPONSE --> RESTORE

    RESTORE -->|"IPs, hostnames restored\nvia token store"| FINAL
    RESTORE -->|"Passwords remain\n[REDACTED] — no way back"| FINAL

